        "timestamp": 1773247095,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. G7 releases record amount of oil stocks to 'calm the markets down' Middle East Issued on: 11/03/2026 - 17:38 Modified: 11/03/2026 - 17:40 G7 leaders have announced the record release of 400 million barrels of oil in response to the war in the Middle East. This represents about twenty days worth of usual oil traffic through the Strait of Hormuz, currently through dangerous to go through due to the threat of Iranian strikes. This initiative aims 'to calm markets down', as FRANCE 24's Philip Turle explains. Strait of Hormuz: US says it destroyed 16 Iranian mine-laying vessels 11/03/2026 Middle East Beirut: FRANCE 24 in the heart of the bombed southern suburbs 11/03/2026 Middle East Volatile oil markets due to Middle East conflict increase jet fuel prices 11/03/2026 Middle East Trump a lot more concern about how war and oil prices will affect midterms 11/03/2026 Middle East Centre of Beirut shocked after Israeli army strikes apartment block 11/03/2026 Middle East UK deploys warship in the Mediterranean to protect British bases in Cyprus 11/03/2026 Middle East Israeli government is undertaking a 'power grab under cover of war' 11/03/2026 Middle East FRANCE 24 speaks to displaced Lebanese in mountains north of Beirut 11/03/2026 Middle East Three ships attacked in Strait of Hormuz as Iran 'weaponises' passage point 11/03/2026 Middle East"
