        "contenuto_esteso": "Advertisement US, Israel war on Iran US Diplomacy US military warns civilians to avoid port facilities used by Iranian navy Ongoing investigation also reportedly found US responsible for deadly missile strike on Iranian elementary school on first day of attacks 2 -MIN READ 2 -MIN Listen in Washington Published: 12:42am, 12 Mar 2026 Updated: 12:58am, 12 Mar 2026 US Central Command (CENTCOM) urged civilians to keep clear of all port facilities in Iran , saying that Iranian military operations justify potential attacks, while an ongoing investigation reportedly found the US to be responsible for a deadly missile strike on an Iranian elementary school. CENTCOM said on Wednesday that the Iranian regime was using civilian ports along the Strait of Hormuz to conduct military operations, which would make the ports legitimate military targets under international law. Civilians should immediately avoid all port facilities, and Iranian dockworkers, administrative personnel and commercial vessel crews should avoid Iranian naval vessels and military equipment, CENTCOM said. Advertisement The warning came as the Strait of Hormuz, a waterway between Iran and Oman that is crucial for international oil shipping, became a central flashpoint in the escalating US-Iran conflict . Regional tensions rise as US and Israeli forces continue to strike Iran and Lebanon Regional tensions rise as US and Israeli forces continue to strike Iran and Lebanon Shipping has effectively ground to a halt since the US launched air strikes against Iran nearly two weeks ago, as the world sees oil and gas prices continue to climb. US President Donald Trump threatened on Tuesday to hit Iran “20 times harder” with “death, fire and fury” if the country blocks the flow of oil and goods through the passage. Advertisement Advertisement Select Voice Select Speed 00:00 00:00 1.00"
